messages:
Name: Alexander González
Nationality: Venezuela
Date of Birth: September 13, 1992
Position: Defender
Current club: Málaga
Segunda División clubs played for: Huesca, Elche, Mirandés, Málaga

Alexander González is an Málaga defender who has appeared in 16 Segunda División games in 2020/2021 since joining the club on 4th January 2021, being selected in the starting XI in 11 of these and being used as a substitute on five occasions.
González last made an appearance in a competition game on May 24, playing 89 minutes for Málaga against Leganés in a 1-0 loss. He has amassed three yellow cards.
Last season for Mirandés, González made 26 Segunda División appearances and created one assist.
González switched to Málaga in January 2021 from Dinamo Bucureşti, for whom he made seven league appearances in total, scoring one goal.
